      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Office of Lands and Survey ¶ Melbourne 3rd Novr 1869 ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ Referring to my letter to you under date of the 1st instant, ¶ See J. McKean to M, 1 November 1869. ¶  ¶ and to your reply thereto, ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.11.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James McKean</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Unit 3, p. 254, VPRS 7936/P1 outward letterbooks of the Secretary for Lands, Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Office of Lands and Survey</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 3rd Novr 1869</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Referring to my letter to you under date of the 1st instant,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. McKean to M, 1 November 1869.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and to your reply thereto,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the same date,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Check.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">We do not have this letter. Surely there must be at least a register entry for it? Given all the fuss and transfer of docs between departments, in the run up to M's d</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">i</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">smissal, who knows where it ended up.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">, especially as it seems some of the documents were requested again when later M was asking to be reinstated, with some grounds for gardens</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have to apprise you that I have decided to place the Botanic Garden at Melbourne and the reserved Crown Lands contiguous thereto under the charge and supervision of Mr. Ferguson.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Ferguson.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">On 27 October 1869 in answer to a question in the Legislative Assembly</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James McKean</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>stated that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">the Government did not intend to appoint any person to specially look after [Forests}. In future they would be looked after from the Botanic Gardens department, which <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he intended to reorganize. About ten days ago, he called for a return of the Botanic Gardens staff, in consequence of his own observations, and the representations of several gentlemen who complained bitterly of the state of the gardens. The return was very unsatisfactory. It showed, in his opinion, that there were more lieutenants than working men. He intended to place Mr. Ferguson at the head of the staff. By this arrangement, Dr. Von Mueller would be relieved of much of the drudgery of the department, and be left more at ease in the scientific branch</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Hansard</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">, session 1869, vol 9, p. 2062). A. Skene to M</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>7 December 1869 referred to this statement when responding to a letter from M that has not been found in which M apparently protested about the implication that his work was not valued.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The decision provoked correspondence in the press. See, for example, W. Lockhart Morton to the editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Argus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">, 5 November 1869, p. 7 (In this edition as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">M69</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">11</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">04</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">W. Lockhart Morton to the editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Argus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">10 November 1869, p. 7 (in this edition as M69-11-09);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Three letters from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">'Pruning Knife'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Weekly times</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">4</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>December 1869</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">, 12 December 1869, 18 December 1869</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as M69-12-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">04, M69-12-11, M69-12-18) were collected with minor changes and an introduction and issued as 'Pruning Knife' (1870).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will have the goodness, therefore, to hand over to Mr Ferguson the control of the Garden and lands referred to, retaining yourself<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the charge of the Museum and Class<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ground for scientific purposes.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedt Servant,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James McKean</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Commissioner of Crown Lands &amp; Survey.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c,<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c,<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
